1
00:00:02,769 --> 00:00:06,762
<i>[ Wind Howling ]</i>

2
00:00:12,278 --> 00:00:15,148
[ Man Shouting, Indistinct ]

3
00:00:15,148 --> 00:00:18,084
[ Shouting, Indistinct ]

4
00:00:18,084 --> 00:00:21,554
Storm is coming !
Move it out !

5
00:00:21,554 --> 00:00:25,547
[ Shouting Continues ]

6
00:00:36,403 --> 00:00:39,305
Last wall ! Pour it on !

7
00:00:39,305 --> 00:00:43,298
<i>Put it up!</i>

8
00:00:45,278 --> 00:00:48,581
This little piece of wood
ain't gonna hold no twister !

9
00:00:48,581 --> 00:00:51,785
- We need to dig a hole !
You know what I'm sayin' ?
- Whaley !

10
00:00:51,785 --> 00:00:55,455
Big hole ! The man ought
to be giving us shovels !

11
00:00:55,455 --> 00:00:59,448
This whole damn place is gonna
blow away. Why even bother ?

12
00:01:01,494 --> 00:01:05,487
- Back me up here !
- Shut up and hold it still !

13
00:01:06,266 --> 00:01:10,259
I know you ain't
talkin' to me.

14
00:01:11,104 --> 00:01:14,541
You're a big man, huh ?
Is that right ?

15
00:01:14,541 --> 00:01:17,477
Charley Potatoes.
Big-ass criminal.

16
00:01:17,477 --> 00:01:20,346
<i>You a bad man ?</i>

17
00:01:20,346 --> 00:01:23,316
You're a little bitch !
That's all you are.

18
00:01:23,316 --> 00:01:27,309
<i>You ain't got no money.</i>
<i>You ain't got nothin'.</i>

19
00:01:29,522 --> 00:01:33,515
I'll hold it still.
[ Laughing ]

20
00:01:35,195 --> 00:01:39,188
Is that still enough for ya ? Huh ?
[ Laughing ]

21
00:01:41,901 --> 00:01:44,671
[ Screaming ]

22
00:01:44,671 --> 00:01:48,575
Put down the hammer, Rawls !
Rawls !

23
00:01:48,575 --> 00:01:52,568
<i>[ Screaming Continues ]</i>

24
00:01:55,215 --> 00:01:59,208
- Messed up old Whaley, did he ?
- Messed him up good.

25
00:01:59,385 --> 00:02:03,256
- Now, what you go and do that for ?
- The man pissed me off, boss.

26
00:02:03,256 --> 00:02:07,249
Who the hell doesn't ?
Box him.

27
00:02:07,427 --> 00:02:10,396
You can't put me in that box.
The storm's coming.

28
00:02:10,396 --> 00:02:12,932
You should've thought of that
before you messed up Whaley.

29
00:02:12,932 --> 00:02:15,869
The hell with Whaley.
You can't put me in that box !

30
00:02:15,869 --> 00:02:19,706
Boss, you can't put me in there !
You can't put me in that box !

31
00:02:19,706 --> 00:02:21,841
<i>You can't do it!</i>

32
00:02:21,841 --> 00:02:24,344
You're going to kill me, boss !

33
00:02:24,344 --> 00:02:26,880
You know they're saying tornado
touchdowns all over the county.

34
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:30,873
I can't be responsible
for acts of God.

35
00:02:36,456 --> 00:02:40,449
- Sorry, Rawls.
- <i>Let me out! Let me out!</i>

36
00:02:42,562 --> 00:02:44,931
[ Grunting ]

37
00:02:44,931 --> 00:02:47,167
<i>Somebody let me out!</i>

38
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:50,503
<i>Help! Somebody!</i>

39
00:02:50,503 --> 00:02:54,496
<i>Somebody help me, please!</i>

40
00:02:59,946 --> 00:03:03,939
<i>[ Men Chattering ]</i>

41
00:03:09,322 --> 00:03:13,315
Oh, hell.

42
00:03:15,895 --> 00:03:19,888
Hello, sir ?
[ Knocks On Door]

43
00:03:37,584 --> 00:03:41,577
Oh, my God.

44
00:04:59,065 --> 00:05:01,067
Should we arrest David Copperfield ?

45
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:04,737
Yes, we should, but not for this.

46
00:05:04,737 --> 00:05:06,572
This is Raybert Fellowes,

47
00:05:06,572 --> 00:05:09,776
<i>superintendent of Road Farm Six,</i>
<i>Mississippi Department of Corrections.</i>

48
00:05:09,776 --> 00:05:13,769
<i>One of his guards found him.</i>
<i>Not a drop of blood in the place.</i>

49
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:17,116
Well, maybe he was killed elsewhere.

50
00:05:17,116 --> 00:05:21,087
Whoever did it took 40 minutes
to do it in the middle of a tornado.

51
00:05:21,087 --> 00:05:24,357
<i>What do you make of that ?</i>

52
00:05:24,357 --> 00:05:26,993
I don't know. It's, uh--

53
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:29,362
It's not a simple bisection.

54
00:05:29,362 --> 00:05:31,964
There's a considerable amount
of his abdomen missing.

55
00:05:31,964 --> 00:05:35,068
<i>It almost looks like a burning,</i>
<i>but it's too localized.</i>

56
00:05:35,068 --> 00:05:38,838
Maybe an industrial acid.

57
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:42,831
There's, uh, no acid
found in his office.

58
00:05:44,477 --> 00:05:47,413
Hmm.

59
00:05:47,413 --> 00:05:49,649
Spontaneous human combustion.

60
00:05:49,649 --> 00:05:53,386
- Scully.
- Isn't that where you're
going with this ?

61
00:05:53,386 --> 00:05:55,488
<i>"Dear Diary: Today my heart leapt...</i>

62
00:05:55,488 --> 00:05:58,858
when Agent Scully suggested
spontaneous human combustion.''

63
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:02,851
There are one or two
somewhat well documented cases.

64
00:06:05,131 --> 00:06:07,567
Mulder, shut up.

65
00:06:07,567 --> 00:06:10,403
<i>Okay, what do</i>
you <i>make of this ?</i>

66
00:06:10,403 --> 00:06:14,396
I don't have a theory,
but I know someone who does.

67
00:06:14,974 --> 00:06:18,967
Hell, yes, Pinker Rawls who did it,
though you got me as to how.

68
00:06:20,079 --> 00:06:22,749
- And who is Pinker Rawls ?
- Inmate.

69
00:06:22,749 --> 00:06:25,885
- Mean son of a bitch.
- Rawls was the prisoner
who supposedly died...

70
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:29,589
in the tornado that preceded
Superintendent Fellowes' murder.

71
00:06:29,589 --> 00:06:32,592
So you're saying
that a ghost did this ?

72
00:06:32,592 --> 00:06:36,585
I'm not putting a word to it.
That's up to y'all. All I know
is that Rawls hated the captain.

73
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:41,067
Captain locked him in the box
when the storm hit, and Rawls
didn't want to be in the box.

74
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:43,202
<i>And when we found the box,</i>

75
00:06:43,202 --> 00:06:47,140
the biggest piece was about
yea big three miles from here.

76
00:06:47,140 --> 00:06:51,133
<i>This whole place was locked</i>
<i>and boarded up tight.</i>

77
00:06:51,511 --> 00:06:55,047
No man got in here.

78
00:06:55,047 --> 00:06:59,040
That's all I'm sayin'.

79
00:07:00,186 --> 00:07:03,589
- So we're looking for a dead man ?
- I disagree.

80
00:07:03,589 --> 00:07:06,025
I think this Pinker Rawls
is still very much alive.

81
00:07:06,025 --> 00:07:08,728
You know, they never
found his body.

82
00:07:08,728 --> 00:07:11,197
Well, at the risk
of further ridicule,

83
00:07:11,197 --> 00:07:14,200
what if this wasn't a murder ?

84
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:17,870
<i>As I understand it, current theory</i>
<i>on spontaneous human combustion...</i>

85
00:07:17,870 --> 00:07:21,073
<i>is that climatic conditions</i>
<i>play a large part.</i>

86
00:07:21,073 --> 00:07:25,066
<i>So possibly a tornado</i>
<i>may fit the bill.</i>

87
00:07:25,211 --> 00:07:27,213
<i>We've got lightning,</i>

88
00:07:27,213 --> 00:07:29,782
static electricity
at a high potential.

89
00:07:29,782 --> 00:07:33,775
I can't argue with that,
but I do think it's murder.

90
00:07:33,953 --> 00:07:37,946
Well, then how did Rawls,
or whoever, do this ?

91
00:07:38,090 --> 00:07:42,083
<i>Uh, how did he get in</i>
<i>and out of a locked office...</i>

92
00:07:42,728 --> 00:07:45,832
and prop a body up against
the inside of a door ?

93
00:07:45,832 --> 00:07:49,825
[ Hollow Sound ]

94
00:08:07,587 --> 00:08:11,157
Termites ?

95
00:08:11,157 --> 00:08:15,150
[ Guard ]
This is all he had in his bunk area.

96
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:19,499
Wilson Pinker Rawls, age 34.

97
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:23,492
Eight years into 30 for robbing
a wire office in Bay St. Louis.

98
00:08:23,769 --> 00:08:26,772
The $90,000 he stole
was never recovered.

99
00:08:26,772 --> 00:08:29,041
Mm, it's not in here.

100
00:08:29,041 --> 00:08:31,577
Hey, look at this.

101
00:08:31,577 --> 00:08:35,570
Ouch.

102
00:08:36,048 --> 00:08:38,117
His record dates to 1978.

103
00:08:38,117 --> 00:08:42,110
Mostly small-time.
History of violence throughout.

104
00:08:45,992 --> 00:08:49,985
I wonder who she is.

105
00:08:57,270 --> 00:08:59,539
- Thanks, cutie.
- [ Chuckles ]

106
00:08:59,539 --> 00:09:03,042
- You broke out the good stuff.
- Well, we're worth the good stuff.

107
00:09:03,042 --> 00:09:05,177
Mmm.

108
00:09:05,177 --> 00:09:07,179
<i>[ TVAudio, Indistinct ]</i>

109
00:09:07,179 --> 00:09:10,216
- Hey, Robert ?
Can I show you something ?
- Hmm ?

110
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:14,209
-Just a little food for thought.
-Wait, sweetie. They're
talking about the tornado.

111
00:09:14,754 --> 00:09:16,756
...Smith and Covington Counties.

112
00:09:16,756 --> 00:09:19,325
Take a look at this video,just in.

113
00:09:19,325 --> 00:09:21,928
Hardest hit was a state prison farm
outside the village of Stringer...

114
00:09:21,928 --> 00:09:24,697
<i>where two deaths are reported</i>
<i>in the wake of the storm.</i>

115
00:09:24,697 --> 00:09:28,134
<i>A funnel cloud with winds</i>
<i>topping 150 miles per hour...</i>

116
00:09:28,134 --> 00:09:30,202
<i>tore through</i>
<i>the isolated work camp,</i>

117
00:09:30,202 --> 00:09:33,706
<i>passing within yards of a barracks</i>
<i>filled with terrified inmates.</i>

118
00:09:33,706 --> 00:09:37,343
<i>Among the dead, Captain Raybert</i>
<i>Fellowes, the farm superintendent,</i>

119
00:09:37,343 --> 00:09:40,646
<i>a 28</i>-<i>year veteran of</i>
<i>the Department of Corrections.</i>

120
00:09:40,646 --> 00:09:43,015
<i>A second casualty</i>
<i>was a prison inmate,</i>

121
00:09:43,015 --> 00:09:46,218
<i>Wilson P. Rawls, age 34</i>--

122
00:09:46,218 --> 00:09:48,688
- Prison authorities say--
- Excuse me.

123
00:09:48,688 --> 00:09:50,690
You okay,June ?

124
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:54,683
<i>...secure the prison from</i>
<i>the oncoming storm. High winds</i>
<i>apparently carried the man away.</i>

125
00:09:54,894 --> 00:09:58,887
<i>Though his body has not been found,</i>
<i>Rawls is presumed dead.</i>

126
00:10:45,311 --> 00:10:48,881
<i>You got a gun pointed at you.</i>
<i>Don't try to run.</i>

127
00:10:48,881 --> 00:10:51,951
I ain't runnin'.

128
00:10:51,951 --> 00:10:55,944
Ah !

129
00:10:56,756 --> 00:10:59,892
Hey ! Hey, that's store property.
Take those off!

130
00:10:59,892 --> 00:11:03,095
Ooh ! There's something so nice about
putting on a brand-new pair of socks.

131
00:11:03,095 --> 00:11:05,097
I don't know what it is.

132
00:11:05,097 --> 00:11:08,300
- I said, take those off, boy !
- Ooh !

133
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:11,070
Ooh. Ooh.
[ Chuckles ]

134
00:11:11,070 --> 00:11:15,063
What you think ?
That's me, right ?

135
00:11:17,943 --> 00:11:20,112
And room to grow in.

136
00:11:20,112 --> 00:11:24,105
You got an attitude, I'll say that.
Get the hell up.

137
00:11:25,985 --> 00:11:29,978
Turn around.
Hands behind the pole.

138
00:11:44,003 --> 00:11:46,372
<i>Yeah, this is Bobby in Security.</i>

139
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:50,365
I've detained an intruder
at the <i>V</i>al-U-Mart on
Nine Mile Road and route 60.

140
00:11:50,843 --> 00:11:53,446
- <i>The door wasn't jimmied.</i>
- <i>[ Handcuffs Clinking ]</i>

141
00:11:53,446 --> 00:11:57,439
<i>I don't know how the hell he got</i>
<i>in here. He was just walking around.</i>

142
00:11:57,950 --> 00:12:01,943
<i>Got him cuffed in the back.</i>
<i>Yeah, I'll hold.</i>

143
00:12:02,755 --> 00:12:06,748
<i>[ Car Horn Honking ]</i>

144
00:12:11,997 --> 00:12:15,990
[ Tires Screeching ]

145
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:20,106
- <i>[ Mulder ] Is that the guy?</i>
- Yeah, could be.

146
00:12:20,106 --> 00:12:22,408
I guess.
It was pretty dark.

147
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:25,377
- How'd he get away ?
- Whoever he was.

148
00:12:25,377 --> 00:12:27,747
You got me.
Guy's like Houdini.

149
00:12:27,747 --> 00:12:31,740
Turned my back, he was gone.
I had him right here.

150
00:12:32,017 --> 00:12:34,854
You had him handcuffed... here ?

151
00:12:34,854 --> 00:12:36,856
Can I see your handcuffs ?

152
00:12:36,856 --> 00:12:40,849
<i>[ Dispatcher On Police Radio,</i>
<i>Indistinct ]</i>

153
00:12:51,137 --> 00:12:55,130
Do we have a last known address
for Pinker Rawls ?

154
00:12:56,308 --> 00:13:00,301
<i>[ Crickets Chirping ]</i>

155
00:13:07,987 --> 00:13:11,980
<i>[ Shatters ]</i>

156
00:13:19,365 --> 00:13:23,358
Hey, hello ?

157
00:13:25,337 --> 00:13:29,241
Rawls ?

158
00:13:29,241 --> 00:13:31,243
What's up ?

159
00:13:31,243 --> 00:13:35,236
You're on the news, man.
They're saying you got killed.

160
00:13:35,548 --> 00:13:39,541
- Where is she ?
-June ? She's gone.

161
00:13:40,019 --> 00:13:44,012
Long gone, man.
She left me, like, four years ago.

162
00:13:44,256 --> 00:13:48,249
You mad 'cause, uh,
her and me shacked up ?

163
00:13:49,028 --> 00:13:51,096
I'm sorry, buddy.

164
00:13:51,096 --> 00:13:55,089
Bo, I want what's mine.

165
00:13:55,367 --> 00:13:59,360
I might have her address.

166
00:14:11,283 --> 00:14:14,854
-You got nothing in there but your nine.
-<i>[ Cocks Hammer ]</i>

167
00:14:14,854 --> 00:14:17,890
Get the hell out of my house.

168
00:14:17,890 --> 00:14:21,883
Bo, you gonna shoot me ?

169
00:14:22,261 --> 00:14:26,254
Boo !

170
00:14:28,133 --> 00:14:31,937
Bah !

171
00:14:31,937 --> 00:14:35,875
You gonna do somethin' ?

172
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:39,868
Hah !

173
00:14:46,085 --> 00:14:50,078
[ Yelling ]

174
00:14:52,491 --> 00:14:56,484
<i>No. No!</i>

175
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:07,006
This is Rawls' last known address.

176
00:15:07,006 --> 00:15:10,999
Security guard's car.

177
00:15:20,052 --> 00:15:24,045
Mulder.

178
00:15:41,473 --> 00:15:43,575
[ Groans ]

179
00:15:43,575 --> 00:15:46,946
[ Groans ]
Gesundheit.

180
00:15:46,946 --> 00:15:50,939
- Oh, my God.
- [ Groans ]

181
00:15:55,955 --> 00:15:57,990
Pistol in his hand.

182
00:15:57,990 --> 00:16:00,125
Slide locked open,
shell casings everywhere.

183
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:02,995
I don't see any bullet holes
anywhere, Mulder.

184
00:16:02,995 --> 00:16:06,265
[ Sighs ]

185
00:16:06,265 --> 00:16:10,258
Don't recognize him from
his driver's license, do you ?

186
00:16:11,303 --> 00:16:14,273
Bo Merkle.
This is his house.

187
00:16:14,273 --> 00:16:18,266
But Rawls used to live here, and he's
come back looking for something.

188
00:16:18,344 --> 00:16:20,512
Ninety thousand dollars.

189
00:16:20,512 --> 00:16:24,505
The wire office robbery eight years ago.
That money hasn't been recovered.

190
00:16:25,217 --> 00:16:27,553
I don't think he
spent that in prison.

191
00:16:27,553 --> 00:16:31,546
I don't think Mr. Merkle did either,
judging by the decor.

192
00:16:31,657 --> 00:16:34,193
Maybe she knows.
That's this house, isn't it ?

193
00:16:34,193 --> 00:16:36,562
Yeah.

194
00:16:36,562 --> 00:16:40,555
- I can run down her name.
- Yeah, I bet Rawls is looking for her.

195
00:16:42,568 --> 00:16:46,561
<i>[ Phone Beeps ]</i>

196
00:16:47,606 --> 00:16:51,599
- [ Creaks ]
- <i>Yeah, this is Special Agent</i>
<i>Dana Scully with the F.B.I.</i>

197
00:16:52,444 --> 00:16:56,437
<i>There's been a murder here</i>
<i>at 922 Washington Avenue inJackson.</i>

198
00:16:57,616 --> 00:17:01,353
<i>I need crime scene support</i>
<i>on</i>-<i>site as soon as possible.</i>

199
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:05,346
<i>Thank you.</i>
<i>Oh, and would you transfer me</i>--

200
00:17:16,602 --> 00:17:20,595
<i>[ Dispatcher On Radio, Indistinct ]</i>

201
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:26,034
Got a name to go with
the face--June Gurwitch.

202
00:17:26,311 --> 00:17:30,304
There's no current address, though,
and no record of her since 1996.

203
00:17:30,516 --> 00:17:34,186
Maybe she changed her name.

204
00:17:34,186 --> 00:17:37,322
Maybe she was afraid
she'd end up like that.

205
00:17:37,322 --> 00:17:40,192
The state police have put out
an A.P.B. on Rawls.

206
00:17:40,192 --> 00:17:43,595
You might warn them not to shoot to
kill. He seems to find that annoying.

207
00:17:43,595 --> 00:17:47,399
- Look, Mulder, even
if those were bullets--
- They are.

208
00:17:47,399 --> 00:17:51,392
Their composition's been changed,just
like the handcuffs and the prison wall.

209
00:17:51,470 --> 00:17:55,174
Even if these were bullets,
there is no way that they
could pass through Rawls...

210
00:17:55,174 --> 00:17:59,167
in the way you're describing,
not without leaving him dead
on the ground for us to find.

211
00:17:59,711 --> 00:18:02,081
I think they went
right through him,

212
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:05,584
like his wrist went through
the handcuffs and like he walked
through that prison wall.

213
00:18:05,584 --> 00:18:07,753
He walks through solid objects ?

214
00:18:07,753 --> 00:18:09,788
Changing their composition
fundamentally--

215
00:18:09,788 --> 00:18:13,781
- making steel brittle,
turning lead bullets into powder.
- And flesh into carbon ?

216
00:18:14,193 --> 00:18:16,895
I don't know how else
to explain what happened
to that prison superintendent...

217
00:18:16,895 --> 00:18:19,798
or to poor Mr. Merkle
who's got no face anymore.

218
00:18:19,798 --> 00:18:23,435
But where's the science in all of this ?
You're talking alchemy.

219
00:18:23,435 --> 00:18:26,905
I'm not saying that it can't
be explained scientifically.
Maybe it's the tornado.

220
00:18:26,905 --> 00:18:30,809
You suggested it yourself.
Unusual climatic conditions,

221
00:18:30,809 --> 00:18:32,845
high electrical potential.

222
00:18:32,845 --> 00:18:36,115
I'm sorry I even brought it up.

223
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:38,584
We both agree on
who he's looking for ?

224
00:18:38,584 --> 00:18:42,577
-June Gurwitch.
- Do we have any idea
how to find June Gurwitch ?

